(1817, 160564, '2012-09-27 15:15:16', '"Furthermore, in contrast to SLCs [spiny lucidum cells], DTCs [non-ivy dendrite-targeting cells], and MFAs [mossy fiber-associated cells], FSBCs [fast-spiking basket cells] showed low-input resistance (143+/-17 M[omega]; measured at the peak hyperpolarization in response to\n-100 pA current injection), fast membrane time constant ([tau membrane] =\n14.5+/- 1.6 ms; single exponential fit), and no prominent sag. PV [parvalbumin]\nimmunopositivity was found in all tested cells (6 of 6 tested),\noften revealed predominantly in the dendrites (Fig. 2A) (note\nthat partial wash-out of the antigen during long recordings may\nhave contributed to the frequently low levels of PV immunoreactivity\nin the soma). CCK [cholecystokinin] and SOM [somatostatin] immunopositivity was not\ndetected (0 of 3 and 0 of 7, respectively) in FSBCs."', 'p 4242 left bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
