(1940, 160765, '2012-09-27 15:15:17', '"Furthermore, we also tested for b-NOS [nitric oxide synthase] immunoreactivity (Fig. 2C,D) (n 40) and found that 46% of alpha-actinin-2-immunoreactive neurons were\npositive for b-NOS. Consistent with the single-cell RT-PCR results,\n50% of NPY[neuropeptide Y]-positive neurons in the SLM [CA1 stratum lacunosum-moleculare] were immunoreactive\nfor b-NOS, supporting the validity of the single-cell RTPCR\nmethod to accurately predict the expression patterns of\nproteins and peptides."', 'p 6778 right bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
