(2158, 160978, '2012-09-27 15:15:21', '"However, VIP[vasoactive intestinal polypeptide]-positive basket cells do not contain parvalbumin (or either of the other two calcium\nbinding proteins known to label interneurons:\ncalbindin and calretinin, see accompanying paper2),\nbut co-localize another neuropeptide, cholecystokinin\n(CCK)."', 'p 331 right bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
